The paper focuses on a system that supports human fact checkers in verifying claims by translating text into SQL queries on an associated database. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as claim text classifiers and cost-based optimization. Therefore, cs.DB (databases) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions tentative execution of query candidates and prioritizing claim verifications, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of NLP techniques such as claim text classifiers suggests a possible connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
